    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>When the server recieves a POST or PUT request with no body, it will hang forever, waiting for additional content (which will not come).</p>

<p>Generally speaking, you should always inspect the Content-length header to check how many bytes need to be read to get the body of the request. If Content-length is 0 or the header is not present, there is no body and you should not try to read it.</p>

<p>I think the problem is in Request.php line 178.</p>

